I’ve been thinking about myself and about whether I should become a trans female.
Let me start from the beginning, when I first learned what “transgender” means. I began widening my viewpoint of what I wanted and imagining what it would be like if I became a woman. There are several reasons why I want to do it.
One reason is that I want to transform myself, almost like a metamorphosis. I have a strong desire to change and not remain the younger version of myself that my parents shaped and expected me to be. I found their idea of raising a child uncomfortable and unhealthy. They wanted me to become overweight and spoiled because they believed that was what a well-cared-for child should be. I did not want that for myself.
Another reason is that I want to be more authentic. I understand that many transgender people feel that their true gender does not match the sex they were assigned at birth. In my case, I find comfort in the idea that none of us choose the circumstances of our birth, and that we should be free to become who we truly are.
The last reason I can remember is that I want to be unique. I want to do something that most people do not do. I want to think beyond established structures and expectations. Like Giorgio Moroder said in Daft Punk’s song “Giorgio by Moroder,” I want the freedom to think and create without limitations, following my own path rather than a predetermined one.

“If I became a female, what should I do?”
I have seen many trans women wearing cute clothes, crossdressing, cosplaying, and wearing wigs. Some are taking Hormone Replacement Therapy (HRT), or what some Chinese communities jokingly call "candies." I especially envy those who were lucky enough to start HRT at a younger age, when puberty had only just begun.
Of course, I became jealous and envious. I do not have enough money, privacy, or supportive friends to talk about these feelings. I also have very little opportunity to gain real-life experience (RLE) because I am a shut-in person. I do not have much support, and I feel that my body would require a lot more work before I could be considered "passable."
